ANC party leader Musalia  Mudavadi  has rallied rift valley region to endorse him for the presidency in 2022 saying he has the region’s best interest at heart. Mudavadi who spoke in Keiyo South constituency  referred to his father’s loyalty and the larger western Kenya support  to  former President Daniel  Moi for 24 years and subsequent elections  as to why the region should return the favour. KANU Chairman Gideon Moi on the other hand was in Khwisero, Kakamega county  where he made a political statement.  